title: For Sale:  .32 ACP Single/double action Hungarian FEG AP MBP Pistol
postcontent:
.32 ACP Single/double action Hungarian FEG AP MBP Pistol .32ACP single/double action just like the pistols themselves are almost straight Walther PP copies with an aluminum frame.These were Hungarian-made, F.E.G. pistols sold throughout Europe from the late 1960's to the mid-Eighties. Most were made to be sold commercially, but I'm sure some were used by the Communist Hungarian police forces for the walking beat cop. The caliber is the key, .32acp, up until the mid-1970's the "common" police caliber in most of Europe. The F.E.G. PA-63 in 9x18mm Makarov was supposed to have been a Hungarian Military sidearm only.

The Ultimate Concealed Carry Pistol: Nighthawk designed this little pistol to allow you to pack the powerful .45 ACP in a small package, but due to its popularity its now also offered in 9mm. A 4.25" bushing barrel allows field strip anywhere, and keeps the weight down when compared to pistols of comparable size with tapered cone barrels.
When it comes time to choose your everyday carry gun there is a lot to consider. You need something that is reliable, accurate, and easy to wear. You need something that you can enjoy shooting a lot, because there is no substitute for practice. That's where the T3 comes in. They designed this pistol to be pleasing to the eye, but also to be a workhorse that can stand up to thousands of rounds.
The T3 has the best features for any gun its size. The frame is based on the Officer model, but for those with large hands, it features an extended magazine well that gives you the length you need to get all your fingers on the grip. The extension also serves another function: the hand-cut geometric angles really add to its beauty. The slide is a 4.25" Commander length that affords a better sight radius.
Another consideration is weight. The T3 actually weighs one ounce lighter than most officer size 1911s. This makes the T3 the first choice for an all-day carry pistol. 
Heinie Slant-Pro Straight Eights Night Sights are standard. White outline front sight with Tritium makes daytime sight acquisition faster, rear sight has only Tritium, so your eyes quickly pick up the front post.
Serrations provide a "no snag" system. Sights, rear of slide, and mainspring housing all have horizontal serrations rather than checkering. The top of the slide is also serrated to reduce glare. A Nighthawk Custom© lightweight aluminum trigger that has been blacked-out using Perma Kote™ breaks between 3.5 and 4 lbs with no creep. When you put all of these features in one package, you come up with the finest carry gun you can own. All you add is practice.

title: For Sale:  NORINCO Copy Winchester M1897 Trench Gun - 12 gauge
postcontent:
NORINCO copy of the Winchester M1897 Trench gun that served with the US military from WWI through Vietnam; imported by Interstate Arms Company. The NORINCO M97 has an 18.5" barrel and is chambered for 12 gauge, 2 and 3/4 inch shells. True to the original military issued M97s, this gun features the correct 6-row heat shield, "US" and Army Ordinance Corp "Flaming Bomb" stamps, sling mounts, and bayonet lug for mounting the US M1917 bayonet. Unlike many NORINCO imports, this gun does not have a trigger disconnect (like the original Winchester 1897s) which allows the gun to be rapidly "slam fired". I bought this gun new and have only fired about 50 shells through it. The gun has a blued finish with hand rubbed American Walnut furniture. The gun is in excellent condition, both mechanically and aesthetically, having only a couple minor scratches on the stock. Comes with a reproduction of the military issue M7 leather sling. This model is currently no longer being imported to the United States.

This shotgun's compact size and rapid pump capabilities make it perfect for any bug-out kit or home defense.

Price: $600 OBO (would prefer to sell, but all reasonable trades will be considered). Serious offers only please.
